The paper proposes a new algorithm for multi-objective optimization that combines deterministic and stochastic search methods to maximize the hypervolume indicator. This falls under the category of optimization and search algorithms, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category as the proposed algorithm uses an evolutionary algorithm for global exploration. 

cs.OH (Other Computer Science) is also likely as the paper does not fit neatly into any specific sub-category and covers a broad range of topics related to optimization and search algorithms. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible sub-category as the paper uses gradient-based methods for local exploration. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also possible as the paper proposes a new algorithm for solving a complex optimization problem. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible sub-category as the paper discusses the performance of the proposed algorithm compared to other state-of-the-art algorithms for multi-objective optimization.
